---

## вҡҷпёҸ How It Works

### 1пёҸвғЈ Define Beans in XML

Beans are defined inside `beans.xml`.

```xml
<bean id="laptop" class="com.practice.Laptop"/>

<bean id="programmer" class="com.practice.Programmer">
    <property name="laptop" ref="laptop"/>
</bean>
```

---

### 2пёҸвғЈ Load Spring IoC Container

Spring loads the configuration using:

```java
ApplicationContext context =
        new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("beans.xml");
```

---

### 3пёҸвғЈ Retrieve Bean from Container

Spring returns the fully configured object.

```java
Programmer programmer = context.getBean("programmer", Programmer.class);
programmer.code();
```

